 &lt;div class="card">
 &lt;h2>Nifty50 on each of it working day&lt;/h2>
 &lt;p>The NSE functions only on weekdays. If we exclude weekends, the number of working days comes down to 261 (365 - 52*2). And then, there comes some more public holidays. This generally varies on each year. The actual working days of the market comes around 250 (+/- 5) days&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>